  "body": "### Description\r\nAs an user and developer, I want to be able to use the `/eth/v1/node/peer_count` endpoint as defined on https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-APIs so that I can quickly get the number of connected peers on my Teku beacon node.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nQuery to the `/eth/v1/node/peer_count` endpoint returns the proper results according to the specs on https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-APIs\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\nQuery to the `/eth/v1/node/peer_count` endpoint returns the following:\r\n```\r\nHTTP/1.1 404 Not Found\r\nContent-Length: 131\r\nContent-Type: application/json\r\nDate: Wed, 19 May 2021 19:36:23 GMT\r\nServer: Javalin\r\n\r\n{\r\n    \"details\": [],\r\n    \"status\": 404,\r\n    \"title\": \"Not found\",\r\n    \"type\": \"https://javalin.io/documentation#notfoundresponse\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n* Software version: teku/v21.5.0/windows-x86_64/adoptopenjdk-java-11\r\n* Java version: openjdk 11.0.11 2021-04-20 - OpenJDK Runtime Environment AdoptOpenJDK-11.0.11+9 (build 11.0.11+9) - OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM AdoptOpenJDK-11.0.11+9 (build 11.0.11+9, mixed mode)\r\n* OS Name & Version: Windows 10\r\n",
